<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Magnetohydrodynamics&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div style="font-size: 95%">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Alfvén, H., "<a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1942Natur.150..405A&amp;db_key=AST&amp;data_type=HTML&amp;format=&amp;high=42ca922c9c21226" class="external text" title="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1942Natur.150..405A&amp;db_key=AST&amp;data_type=HTML&amp;format=&amp;high=42ca922c9c21226" rel="nofollow">Existence of electromagnetic-hydrodynamic waves</a>" (1942) <i>Nature</i>, Vol. 150, pp. 405</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.oulu.fi/~spaceweb/textbook/mhdwaves.html" class="external text" title="http://www.oulu.fi/~spaceweb/textbook/mhdwaves.html" rel="nofollow">MHD waves [Oulu]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> M. J. Lighthill, "Studies on MHD waves and other anisotropic wave motion," <i>Phil. Trans. Roy. Soc.</i>, London, vol. 252A, pp. 397-430, 1960.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> E.A. Witalis, "<a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1986ITPS...14..842W&amp;db_key=PHY&amp;data_type=HTML&amp;format=&amp;high=42ca922c9c11756" class="external text" title="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1986ITPS...14..842W&amp;db_key=PHY&amp;data_type=HTML&amp;format=&amp;high=42ca922c9c11756" rel="nofollow">Hall Magnetohydrodynamics and Its Applications to Laboratory and Cosmic Plasma</a>", <i>IEEE Transactions on Plasma Science</i> (ISSN 0093-3813), vol. PS-14, Dec. 1986, p. 842-848.</li>
<li id="cite_note-space-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-space_4-0" title="">^</a></b> W. Baumjohann and R. A. Treumann, <i>Basic Space Plasma Physics</i>, Imperial College Press, 1997</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://navier.stanford.edu/PIG/C4_S9.pdf" class="external free" title="http://navier.stanford.edu/PIG/C4_S9.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://navier.stanford.edu/PIG/C4_S9.pdf</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> Alfvén, H., "<a href="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?1942StoAn..14....9A" class="external text" title="http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?1942StoAn..14....9A" rel="nofollow">On the cosmogony of the solar system III", <i>Stockholms Observatoriums Annaler</i></a>, vol. 14, pp.9.1-9.29</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.phy6.org/earthmag/NSTA1C.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.phy6.org/earthmag/NSTA1C.htm" rel="nofollow">Dynamos in Nature</a> by David P. Stern</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> McKetta J McKetta, "<a href="http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0824726170&amp;id=U8Bd7TOcma4C&amp;pg=PA127&amp;lpg=PA127&amp;dq=faraday+%22waterloo+bridge%22+mhd&amp;sig=5Q8nbTh6flsGzyFVH36cCAcpUh0" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0824726170&amp;id=U8Bd7TOcma4C&amp;pg=PA127&amp;lpg=PA127&amp;dq=faraday+%22waterloo+bridge%22+mhd&amp;sig=5Q8nbTh6flsGzyFVH36cCAcpUh0" rel="nofollow">Encyclopedia of Chemical Processing and Design: Volume 66</a>" (1999)</li>
